phyloseq2 = subset_taxa(phylum_data365, phylum %in% top_phylum)
pseqs = list(c(phyloseq1, phyloseq2))
pesudo = 0; zero_cut = 0.9; corr_cut = 0.5; lib_cut = 0
wins_quant = c(0.05, 0.95); method = "pearson"; soft = FALSE; thresh_len = 20
n_cv = 10; seed = 123; thresh_hard = 0.3; max_p = 0.005; n_cl = 5

linear_phy_365 = secom_linear(pseqs, pesudo, zero_cut, corr_cut, lib_cut, 
                             wins_quant, method, soft, thresh_len, n_cv, 
                             seed, thresh_hard, max_p, n_cl)
Warning in sparse_linear(mat = t(y_hat), wins_quant, method, soft, thresh_len,  :

There are some pairs of taxa that have insufficient (< 10) overlapping samples.
Proceed with caution since the point estimates for these pairs are unstable.
For pairs of taxa with no overlapping samples, the point estimates will be replaced with 0s,
and the corresponding p-values will be replaced with 1s.
Please check `mat_cooccur` for details about the co-occurrence pattern.
